{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "sc3-ht-mc-bh-001",
    "name": "Stables-HT-multi-contract-BH-1",
    "description": "ACTUS: HYBRID TREASURY MANAGEMENT — Multi-Contract Behavioral Simulation\n\nMODELS A STABLECOIN PORTFOLIO with $100K token supply backed by:\n  Cash Reserve (PAM):     $5,000  — immediate liquidity, tracked daily\n  T-Bill 4-Week (PAM):    $25,000 — matures Mar 15, injects cash on maturity\n  T-Bill 8-Week (PAM):    $25,000 — matures Mar 30, second cash injection\n  T-Bill 13-Week (PAM):   $25,000 — matures Apr 15, third cash injection\n  T-Bill 26-Week (PAM):   $23,000 — matures Jun 15, long-dated reserve\n  TOTAL RESERVES:         $103,000 (103% backing)\n\nCASH TRACKING ACROSS CONTRACTS:\n  Day 1:  Cash = $5,000 (5% liquidity — thin)\n  Day 8:  Cash = $2,800 (redemption drain erodes cash)\n  Day 15: Cash = $28,300 (T-Bill-4W matures → +$25,000 cash spike)\n  Day 18: Cash = $25,500 (some cash deployed to new T-bill purchase)\n  Day 20: Cash = $23,000 (continued outflow)\n  Day 30: Cash = $48,500 (T-Bill-8W matures → +$25,000 second spike)\n\nINTEGRATED BEHAVIORAL MODEL:\n  BackingRatioModel    — monitors reserve/supply ratio + liquidity threshold\n  MaturityLadderModel  — drives T-bill roll decisions based on peg risk score\n  ConcentrationDriftModel — tracks HHI across cash + 4 T-bill buckets\n\n  All three models fire at every epoch. The combined signal tells you:\n    Is the portfolio adequately backed? (BackingRatio)\n    Should we shorten tenor / hold cash / liquidate? (MaturityLadder)\n    Is the portfolio dangerously concentrated? (ConcentrationDrift)\n\nSCENARIO ARC (30 days):\n  Days 1-7:   Healthy. All models return 0.0. Normal operations.\n  Days 8-14:  Stress. Backing drops below 100%. Cash drains to 2.8%.\n              MaturityLadder escalates from NORMAL_ROLL → SHORTEN → CASH_RETENTION.\n              ConcentrationDrift: cash share drops below 5%, T-bills dominate.\n  Day 15:     INFLECTION. T-Bill-4W matures. Cash spikes from $2.8K → $28.3K.\n              BackingRatio recovers. Concentration shifts toward cash (28%).\n  Days 16-29: Recovery. MaturityLadder returns to NORMAL_ROLL.\n              ConcentrationDrift normalizes as cash is redeployed.\n  Day 30:     T-Bill-8W matures. Second cash spike. Portfolio rebalanced.\n\nAPI ENDPOINTS:\n  Risk Service:  localhost:8082\n  Sim Engine:    localhost:8083\n\nOpen Postman Console (Ctrl+Alt+C) before running.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    {"key": "actus_risk_host", "value": "34.203.247.32:8082"},
